A
B
\alpha=sup(A)
\beta=sup(B)
C = \{ab | a \in A, b \in B\}
C
\alpha \beta = sup(C)
\alpha \geq a \;\forall \;a\in A
\beta \geq b \;\forall \;b\in B
\alpha \beta \geq ab \;\forall \;a\in A,b\in B
\alpha \beta = sup(C)
\alpha \beta
C
\epsilon > 0
\epsilon < 3\alpha\beta
a \in A
a+\frac{\epsilon}{3\beta} > \alpha
b \in B
b + \frac{\epsilon}{3\alpha} > \beta
C \ni ab
ab + \epsilon > \alpha\beta
\epsilon>0
   \alpha\beta < \left(a + \frac{\epsilon}{3\beta}\right)\left(b + \frac{\epsilon}{3\alpha}\right) = ab + \frac{a\epsilon}{3\alpha} + \frac{b\epsilon}{3\beta}+\frac{\epsilon^2}{9\alpha\beta} < ab + \frac{\epsilon}{3} + \frac{\epsilon}{3} + \frac{\epsilon}{3} 
